West China Cement Plans 3 Billion Yuan of Investment, SCMP Says

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-03-03T21:52:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/west-china-cement-plans-3-billion-yuan-of-investment-scmp-says.html
West China Cement Ltd. plans to
spend about 3 billion yuan ($456 million) between 2012 and 2016
expanding production capacity to 30 million metric tons, the  South China Morning Post  said, citing Chairman Zhang Jimin.  The company had capacity of 12.5 million tons last year,
and plans to spend 1.4 billion yuan this year on expansion, the
Hong Kong-based English-language newspaper reported today. West
China plans to pay for growth with its own cash, the Post said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  